                    <coeff>4</coeff>
                  </number>
                  <unit>s</unit>
                </unit_number> </latex>:</para>
                <para>The displacement is equal to the area under the whole graph (top and bottom). Remember that an
                area under the time line must be subtracted:</para>
                <para>Area under graph = Area of triangle 1 + Area of triangle 2</para>
                <para>
                  <latex>\text{Area}=\frac{1}{2}bh+\frac{1}{2}bh</latex>
                </para>
                <para>
                  <latex>\text{Area}=\left(\frac{1}{2}\times 2\times 
                  <number>19.6</number>\right)+\left(\frac{1}{2}\times 2\times \left(
